Tripler v. Mayor, Etc., of City of New York. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 31, 1892.) Action by Isabel S. Tripler against the mayor, éte., of the city of New York.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and O’Brien and Ingraham JJ.

No opinion. Motion denied. See 6 N. Y. Supp. 48; 17 N. Y. Supp. 750; 26 N. E. Rep. 721.
